text:
While some may say they are pricey, but the coffee is good, they use Hainanese bread that is well toasted, with a nice slab of butter and an even spread of kaya (not the square sandwich bread and barely there kaya and butter).

The eggs... are also much larger than the usual ones. For a hawker stall in a wet market, this is very worth the money.
Tried yuan yang-c($1.50) is smooth, less sweet, thick in coffee and tea. 9/10
Tried this stall and was surprised that their kopi-o, it was really good and highly recommend
Teh o peng is not bad. But on the higher end pricing
Expensive and bland diluted coffee in tall but skinny cup for $2.
